rralPage component -->\n   377→- [ ] Code generation works and displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378→- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379→- [ ] Custom code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380→- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381→- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382→- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383→- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   384→- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   385→\n   386→#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n   387→\n   388→In the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   389→\n   390→**Layout:**\n   391→- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   392→- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   393→- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   394→- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   395→\n   396→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   397→- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   398→- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399→- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   400→- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   401→- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   402→\n   403→#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   404→\n   405→Thin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   406→\n   407→```typescript\n   408→const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   409→\n   410→export async function generateReferralCode(token: string, custom?: string);\n   411→export async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   412→export async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   413→export async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   414→export async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   415→export async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   416→export async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   417→```\n   418→\n   419→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   420→- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   421→- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422→- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   423→- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   424→\n   425→#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n   426→\n   427→A hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   428→\n   429→```typescript\n   430→// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   431→export function useReferralApply() {\n   432→  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   433→  const { address } = useWallet();\n   434→\n   435→  useEffect(() => {\n   436→    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   437→    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   438→    if (!stored) return;\n   439→    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   440→    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   441→      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   442→      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   443→  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   444→}\n   445→```\n   446→\n   447→Mount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   448→\n   449→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   450→- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   451→- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452→- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453→- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454→- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   455→- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   456→\n   457→### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   458→\n   459→The referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   460→\n   461→**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   462→1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   463→2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n   464→3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   465→4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   466→\n   467→**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   468→1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   469→2. If found → use KOL rate\n   470→3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   471→\n   472→**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   473→\n   474→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   475→- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   476→- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   477→- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   478→- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   479→- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   480→- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   481→- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n   482→\n   483→---\n   484→\n   485→### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   486→\n   487→Referral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   488→\n   489→**Event types (v1):**\n   490→- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   491→\n   492→Note: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   493→\n   494→**Payload contract:**\n   495→\n   496→`referral.claim_requested`\n   497→```json\n   498→{\n   499→  \"claimId\": \"uuid\","}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19089f60-8377-4442-8359-fb07c65e7a26","uuid":"cb667bf9-8c8b-4221-9602-96f175dc16af","timestamp":"2026-03-25T08:53:16.413Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - Optional: \"Customize code\" link → inline edit field to set custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { custom: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code generation works and displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Custom code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function generateReferralCode(token: string, custom?: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found → use KOL rate\n3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{\n  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",","numLines":150,"startLine":350,"totalLines":717}}}
